@startuml network-scenario-no-vpn
!include _standard-style.puml
title **Scenario C — Outside Corporate Network, No VPN**
caption INSIDE_CN=false | Proxy optional (falls back to DIRECT) | No firewall filtering

left to right direction

' === WORKSTATION ===
rectangle "**Workstation** (localhost)" as WS #F0FFF0 {

  rectangle "Local Proxy (per OS)" as PROXY #FFF8E1 {
    component "**macOS**: Proxydetox :3128\nPAC fetch fails → DIRECT mode" as mac_proxy <<core>>
    component "**Windows**: px :3128\nFalls back to DIRECT" as win_proxy <<core>>
    component "**WSL**: CNTLM :3128\nor unset https_proxy entirely" as wsl_proxy <<core>>
    component "**Linux**: CNTLM :3128\nor unset https_proxy" as lnx_proxy <<core>>

    note bottom of PROXY
      **PAC server unreachable** (no corporate DNS)
      → Local proxy falls back to DIRECT connections
      → Alternatively: unset https_proxy for direct access
      **Kerberos KDC unreachable** → ticket expires, no renewal
      This is **not a problem** — no corporate proxy to authenticate to
    end note
  }

  rectangle "Applications" as APPS #FFFFFF {
    component "Browser" as browser <<cli>>
    component "VS Code + Copilot" as vscode <<cli>>
    component "Git (HTTPS)" as git_https <<cli>>
    component "Git (SSH)" as git_ssh <<cli>>
    component "curl / npm / Docker" as cli_tools <<cli>>
  }

  rectangle "Environment" as CFG #F3E5F5 {
    component "https_proxy=http://127.0.0.1:3128 (proxy in DIRECT mode)\nor unset https_proxy (bypass proxy entirely)\nno_proxy=localhost,*.bmwgroup.net" as env <<util>>
  }
}

' === HOME NETWORK ===
rectangle "**Home Network / ISP**" as HOME #E3F2FD {
  component "**ISP Router**\nNAT, DHCP, ISP DNS" as router <<infra>>
  note bottom of router
    No corporate DNS → *.bmwgroup.net does NOT resolve
    No URL-category filtering
    No SSL inspection
    Port 22 open (no firewall blocking SSH)
  end note
}

' === ENDPOINTS ===
rectangle "**External Endpoints**" as EXT #E8F4FD {
  component "**cc-github.bmwgroup.net**\nGHE :443 / :22" as ghe <<api>>
  component "**api.github.com**\nCopilot :443" as gh_api <<api>>
  component "**api.anthropic.com**\nClaude :443" as anthropic <<api>>
  component "**npm / Docker**\nregistries :443" as registries <<api>>
}

' === FLOW ===
' Apps → proxy (DIRECT mode) or direct
browser --> mac_proxy
vscode --> mac_proxy
cli_tools --> mac_proxy
git_https --> mac_proxy
git_ssh -[#43A047,bold]-> router : SSH :22 (direct)

' Proxy DIRECT → router → internet
mac_proxy -[#43A047,bold]-> router : DIRECT (no upstream proxy)
win_proxy -[#43A047,bold]-> router : DIRECT
wsl_proxy -[#43A047,bold]-> router : DIRECT
lnx_proxy -[#43A047,bold]-> router : DIRECT

' Router → endpoints (all allowed)
router -[#43A047,bold]-> gh_api : ✓ Allowed :443
router -[#43A047,bold]-> anthropic : ✓ **Allowed** :443\n(no URL filter!)
router -[#43A047,bold]-> registries : ✓ Allowed :443
router -[#43A047,bold]-> ghe : ✓ SSH :22 (direct)
router -[#E53935,dashed]-> ghe : ✗ HTTPS :443 to GHE\n(internal DNS required)

' === HEALTH MONITORING ===
rectangle "**Health Monitoring** (coding/bin/coding)" as HEALTH #E1BEE7 {
  note as hn
    **Detection**: DNS for muc.proxy-pac.bmwgroup.net FAILS
    → INSIDE_CN=false → network=open
    **Proxy**: Port 3128 may still listen (DIRECT mode) or be stopped
    **Auto-heal**: If proxy was ON, detect-network.sh may toggle it OFF
    or leave Proxydetox in DIRECT fallback mode
    **Status line**: N:OPEN P:OFF LLM:● (Claude available!)
    **Important**: Claude/Anthropic API is now reachable (no firewall)
  end note
}

' === OS-SPECIFIC NOTES ===
note as os_notes
  **OS-Specific Configuration (outside CN, no VPN):**

  **macOS**: Proxydetox stays running, PAC fetch fails → DIRECT mode.
  No action needed — transparent fallback.

  **Windows**: px may need manual stop or will timeout on proxy auth.
  System proxy (WinHTTP) should be cleared or set to direct.

  **WSL / Linux**: Simplest approach: unset https_proxy in shell profile.
  .netrc credentials are irrelevant (no corporate proxy).
  Alternative: leave CNTLM running — it will CONNECT-forward without auth.

  **All platforms**: SSH to cc-github.bmwgroup.net works on port 22
  (no firewall), but DNS resolution requires /etc/hosts entry or
  VPN. SSH to github.com works natively.
end note

legend bottom
  |= Protocol |= Port |= Auth |= Status (no VPN) |
  | HTTPS (Copilot) | 443 | OAuth Bearer | ✓ Works (direct) |
  | HTTPS (Claude) | 443 | API Key | ✓ **Works** (no firewall!) |
  | HTTPS (Git) | 443 | GCM / OAuth | ✓ Works (public repos / github.com) |
  | SSH (Git) | 22 | SSH Key | ✓ Works (port open, no firewall) |
  | HTTPS (GHE internal) | 443 | SSO/OAuth | ✗ DNS fails (internal only) |
end legend

@enduml
